Definition.WordDefinition: September \Sep*tem"ber\, n. [L., fr. septem seven, as being the seventh month of the Roman year, which began with March: cf. F. septembre. See {Seven}.] The ninth month of the year, containing thurty days. [1913 Webster]
September n : the month following August and preceding October [syn: {Sep}, {Sept}]
